enforceForTSTypes.description:
When `enforceForTSTypes` is enabled, this rule also applies to TypeScript interfaces
and type aliases.

Examples of **incorrect** TypeScript code:
```ts
interface Foo {
get a(): string;
someProperty: string;
set a(value: string);
}

type Bar = {
get b(): string;
someProperty: string;
set b(value: string);
};
```

Examples of **correct** TypeScript code:
```ts
interface Foo {
get a(): string;
set a(value: string);
someProperty: string;
}

type Bar = {
get b(): string;
set b(value: string);
someProperty: string;
};
```

