allowPrimitiveModules.description:
If `allowPrimitiveModules` option is set to true, the following is valid:

```js
module.exports = "foo";
module.exports = function rule(context) {
return { /* ... */ };
};
```

but this is still reported:

```js
module.exports = { x: "y" };
exports.z = function bark() { /* ... */ };
```

